{"type":"message","id":"7449f1ce","parentId":"4b4cac47","timestamp":"2026-03-27T23:44:03.348Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the sessions_list result, the only session is the cron job itself - \"agent:main:cron:3709e1d2-67b1-4eff-92e4-b586ec802978\". This is the cron session, not a user conversation. The last message was from the assistant (me) just now, and before that the cron triggered. There's no actual user conversation happening.\n\nLet me check if there are any other sessions that might be user conversations. The \"kind\" is \"other\" which seems to be the cron job itself. Let me check if there are any sessions with kind \"user\" or \"session\" that indicate real user conversations.\n\nActually, the only session returned is the cron session itself. There are no user conversations. So I should proceed with autonomous learning.\n\nLet me search for information about enterprise digital transformation, smart security, network system integration, and IT operations services - topics related to Daojian Network's business.","thinkingSignature":"a94c785f83a9f92bd6ed4cf62e6f6bdfaac137ae401fd4731a03a6567ecb35b1"},{"type":"text","text":"检测到当前仅有 cron 任务自身的会话（无实际用户对话），执行自主学习。\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mp33vwphbu8b_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/skills/miaoda-web-search/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":868,"output":260,"cacheRead":43981,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45109,"cost":{"input":0.0002604,"output":0.000312,"cacheRead":0.00131943,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00189183}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774655035251}}
